# Observable Plot Syntax

## Basic Pattern

```js
Plot.markType(data, {x: "column1", y: "column2"}).plot()
```

## Common Marks

| Mark | Use |
|------|-----|
| `dot` | Scatter plots |
| `line`, `lineY` | Line charts |
| `barX`, `barY` | Bar charts |
| `areaY` | Area charts |
| `rectY`, `rectX` | Histograms, heatmaps |
| `cell` | Heatmaps (ordinal) |
| `text` | Labels |
| `ruleX`, `ruleY` | Reference lines |

## Layering Marks

Combine multiple marks with the `marks` array:
```js
Plot.plot({
  marks: [
    Plot.ruleY([0]),
    Plot.lineY(data, {x: "date", y: "value"}),
    Plot.dot(data, {x: "date", y: "value"})
  ]
})
```

## Common Options

```js
Plot.plot({
  width: 800,
  height: 400,
  y: {grid: true, label: "Value"},
  x: {label: "Date"},
  color: {legend: true},
  marks: [...]
})
```

## Transforms

- `Plot.binX({y: "count"}, {x: "column"})` - histogram binning
- `Plot.groupX({y: "count"}, {x: "category"})` - group by category
- `Plot.sort({x: "y"}, {x: "cat", y: "val"})` - sort by value
